    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix precision loss in bfly5 DC component calculation\n\n### Summary\nThe `bfly5` function in the DFT implementation was experiencing precision loss due to nested saturated additions when computing the DC component (y0). This caused downstream FFT computations to produce incorrect results, particularly noticeable when processing large input signals.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Modified the DC component calculation in `bfly5` to use sequential saturated additions instead of nested ones, improving numerical stability.\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may observe this issue as:\n- Incorrect FFT output when processing signals with large dynamic range\n- Mismatch between expected and actual frequency domain representation\n- Signal distortion in OFDM modulation/demodulation chains that rely on these DFT functions\n\nThe issue becomes more pronounced with input signals that cause intermediate addition results to approach the int16_t saturation limits, where nested `simde_mm_adds_epi16` operations would clamp values prematurely, affecting the final DC component calculation.\n"
}